      "description": "Two-loop non-planar 6-point integral with massless internal propagators, obtained from the sunrise graph by inserting external legs on the top arc, the bottom arc, and two legs on the middle horizontal line; the two horizontal outer legs are massive, the inserted legs are massless. This is the headline proof-of-concept example of the paper, demonstrating that two-loop multi-leg non-planar integrals can be computed with the FBI representation. Computed numerically to 6-digit precision via DCT; 12826 sample points, 2.91 ms/point. Cross-checked against AMFlow. Called graph $e_6$ in Table I of the paper.",
